        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Water staining on cellar wall below the cooling unit access panel; condensate pump cycling continuously without ever completing a discharge.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Condensate drain line clogged with biofilm and calcium deposits — coastal installation with hard-water condensate, last drain service was at original install 6 years prior. Pump itself was operating; it just had nothing to discharge into. Adjacent racks showed early moisture staining; caught before structural damage.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Drain line clearing and full flush, condensate pump cleaning, biofilm treatment, condensate path verification. Recommended 18-month drain inspection interval going forward.</p>
